{"key":"processedPost-8838986","value":{"id":8838986,"first":8822223,"last":8961379,"when":1219895586,"utime":"08/28/08 06:53 AM","content":"Congrats on your grow!<br />Liquid coffee will definitely help your cakes, but the downside is it puts them at greater risk of contamination. I like to add a tablespoon of gypsum to the basic recipe for five jars; 1 cup brf, 1 cup water, and 2 cups verm. Little else that you can add to cakes is going to help because brown rice flour is really about as good as it gets.&nbsp; If you have a health food store nearby, you can buy rice bran cereal in the refrigerated section and use it instead of brown rice flour.&nbsp; Brans are generally more nutritious for mushrooms than flours.<br />I've tried the tek with most cereal grains, and they all work, but none really better than brown rice, and most grain flours will need to be pressure cooked rather than just steamed.<br />RR","title":"Re: Consolidated Teks on Ways to Boost Nitrogen"}}